main event: Three unidentified objects were observed in the sky above North Brunswick, New Jersey during dusk in July 1962.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 1 minute.,The objects were reported to have moved from southeast to northwest.,No photographs or physical evidence were found.,The conclusion of the report categorized the sighting as astronomical, possibly a star or planet.,The report was part of the Project Blue Book investigation into UFO sightings.
